        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:49AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 248 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Possum Kingdom Lake, or 9 miles southeast of Graham,
moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bryson around 300 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Jermyn, Antelope,
Jean, and Loving.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
